article.headline: Harrison scores 22, Grand Canyon downs Louisiana Tech 73-70

images.name: Tyon Grant-Foster elevates for the big-time swat
images.caption: Tyon Grant-Foster elevates for the big-time swat

article.linkText: Harrison scores 22, Grand Canyon downs Louisiana Tech 73-70
article.story: PHOENIX -- — Rayshon Harrison had 22 points in Grand Canyon's 73-70 victory over Louisiana Tech on Saturday night. Harrison added five assists for the Antelopes (12-1). Tyon Grant-Foster scored 13 points while shooting 3 for 12 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 6 of 6 from the free-throw line. Gabe McGlothan shot 4 for 9, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points, while adding six rebounds. The Antelopes extended their winning streak to nine games. Daniel Batcho led the way for the Bulldogs (9-5) with 16 points and six rebounds. Tahlik Chavez added 16 points and two steals for Louisiana Tech. In addition, Isaiah Crawford finished with 13 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
